additionalType: "ShortStory"
name: "Monitoring tourism in line with sustainable development is progressing but more is needed"
text: "National monitoring based on the Tourism Satellite Accounts and the System of Environmental Economic Accounts provides a good indication of a country’s capacity to measure the economic and environmental sustainability of tourism. In 2019, a record 99 countries used at least one table under the accounts for evaluating key tourism sustainability indicators. A subsequent decline in use from 2020 to 2022 was likely due to a natural lag in data production. While global monitoring capacities have improved across all regions since 2008, in most, less than 50 per cent of countries can report data."
